22// The "header" of the full deopt data for an optimized wasm function containing
23// overall counts used to access the unerlying translated values, literals etc.
24struct WasmDeoptData {
25 uint32_t entry_count = 0; // Count of deopt points.
26 uint32_t translation_array_size = 0;
27 uint32_t deopt_literals_size = 0;
28 // The offset inside the code to the first deopt builtin call instruction.
29 // This is used to map a pc back to a the "deopt index".
30 int deopt_exit_start_offset = 0;
31 // The count of eager deopt points.
32 int eager_deopt_count = 0;
33};
34
35struct WasmDeoptEntry {
36 // The wire bytes offset of the deopt point. This is used to map a deopt entry
37 // to a liftoff deopt point.
38 BytecodeOffset bytecode_offset = BytecodeOffset::None();
39 // The index inside the translations array at which this deopt entry starts.
40 // (The translations array is shared for all deopt points of a function.)
41 int translation_index = -1;
42};
43
44// A view to access the deopt data stored in the WasmCode's metadata as raw
45// bytes.
46class WasmDeoptView {
47 public:
48 explicit WasmDeoptView(base::Vector<const uint8_t> deopt_data)
49 : deopt_data_(deopt_data) {
50 if (!deopt_data.empty()) {
51 static_assert(std::is_trivially_copy_assignable_v<WasmDeoptData>);
52 DCHECK_GE(deopt_data_.size(), sizeof(WasmDeoptData));
53 std::memcpy(&base_data_, deopt_data_.begin(), sizeof(base_data_));
54 }
55 }
56
57 bool HasDeoptData() const { return !deopt_data_.empty(); }
58
59 const WasmDeoptData& GetDeoptData() const {
60 DCHECK(HasDeoptData());
61 return base_data_;
62 }
63
64 base::Vector<const uint8_t> GetTranslationsArray() const {
65 DCHECK(HasDeoptData());
66 return {deopt_data_.begin() + sizeof(base_data_),
67 base_data_.translation_array_size};
68 }
69
70 WasmDeoptEntry GetDeoptEntry(uint32_t deopt_index) const {
71 DCHECK(HasDeoptData());
72 DCHECK(deopt_index < base_data_.entry_count);
73 const uint8_t* begin = deopt_data_.begin() + sizeof(base_data_) +
74 base_data_.translation_array_size;
75 return base::ReadUnalignedValue<WasmDeoptEntry>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(
76 begin + sizeof(WasmDeoptEntry) * deopt_index));
77 }
78
79 std::vector<DeoptimizationLiteral> BuildDeoptimizationLiteralArray();
80
81 private:
82 base::Vector<const uint8_t> deopt_data_;
83 WasmDeoptData base_data_;
84};
85
86class WasmDeoptDataProcessor {
87 public:
88 static base::OwnedVector<uint8_t> Serialize(
89 int deopt_exit_start_offset, int eager_deopt_count,
90 base::Vector<const uint8_t> translation_array,
91 base::Vector<wasm::WasmDeoptEntry> deopt_entries,
92 const ZoneDeque<DeoptimizationLiteral>& deopt_literals);
93};

95// The frame "layout" of a liftoff function for a single deopt point.
96struct LiftoffFrameDescription {
97 uint32_t wire_bytes_offset = 0;
98 uint32_t pc_offset = 0;
99 std::vector<LiftoffVarState> var_state = {};
100 // If the trusted_instance is cached in a register additionally to the stack
101 // slot, this register needs to be updated as well.
102 // TODO(14667): The memory start and memory instance are other fields that can
103 // be cached in liftoff and need to be initialized when performing a deopt.
104 Register trusted_instance = no_reg;
105};
106
107// The set of frame descriptions for all deopt points for a single liftoff
108// function.
109struct LiftoffFrameDescriptionsForDeopt {
110 std::vector<LiftoffFrameDescription> descriptions;
111 int total_frame_size = 0;
112};
